Package: drmSEM
Title: Distributional Piecewise Structural Equation Models on 'drmTMB'
Version: 0.5.0
Authors@R:
    person("Shinichi", "Nakagawa", email = "itchyshin@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A distributional piecewise structural equation modelling
    (SEM) layer built on top of the 'drmTMB' fitting engine. Causal paths
    can target not only the expected response (mu) but also residual scale
    (sigma), shape (nu), zero-inflation (zi), hurdle probability (hu),
    random-effect scale (sd(group)), and bivariate residual correlation
    (rho12). The package provides graph validation, component-labelled path
    tables, d-separation tests over observed responses, and simulation-based
    direct, indirect, and total effects on the link and response scales. It
    does not fit models itself; each endogenous node is one 'drmTMB' fit.
